squatter
Homonym Number: 3
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:often renting from the Crown vast tracts of land for pasturage at an almost nominal sum. The term is still frequently, but incorrectly, used for a man rearing and running stock on freehold land.Pastoralist is now the more favoured term.
Origin:
